# Copy to /etc/forge-fleet/forge-fleet.env (mode 0600) and set values.
# Referenced by forge-fleet.service via EnvironmentFile=.
# Created automatically on first system install (install-update.sh / git-install.sh) if missing.

# Required when binding beyond loopback (see forge-fleet README).
FLEET_BEARER_TOKEN=change-me

# Optional
# When Caddy (or another reverse proxy) injects Authorization on loopback, set 1 so /v1/*
# still requires a bearer (see docs/CADDY-SYSTEMD.md).
# FLEET_ENFORCE_BEARER=1
#
# Admin “Update from Git” (POST /v1/admin/git-self-update): path to the **git clone** when the
# running tree has no .git (e.g. rsync excludes .git from /opt or ~/.local/share/forge-fleet).
# install-update.sh / install-user.sh set this automatically from the source checkout when it has .git.
# The service user must be able to read/write that checkout for git pull (see README).
# Example (manual override): FLEET_GIT_ROOT=/home/you/forge-fleet
# Optional shell after successful git (instead of update-user.sh): FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_POST_GIT_COMMAND
# Optional: force admin "Update from git" behavior — user (default) vs system (/opt install shows root paste command):
# FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_INSTALL_PROFILE=user
# FLEET_SELF_UPDATE_INSTALL_PROFILE=system
# Same path Lenses uses as workspace root (where ``.lenses-local/`` lives). When set, Test Fleet writes
# ``.lenses-local/fleet-test-attention.json`` so Studio can show the Attention bell item.
# FLEET_LENSES_WORKSPACE_ROOT=/abs/path/to/your/repo-or-workspace
# FLEET_FORGE_CONSOLE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
# FLEET_GIT_SHA=

# Telemetry (SQLite telemetry_samples + cumulative kWh in fleet_energy_ledger; optional)
# FLEET_TELEMETRY_INTERVAL_S=60
# FLEET_TELEMETRY_RETENTION_DAYS=730
# (0 = never delete old samples)
#
# install-user.sh / install-update.sh install forge-fleet-telemetry.timer, which runs
# ``python -m fleet_server.telemetry_sampler`` (~1/min) so rows are written even when the
# HTTP service is stopped. Same FLEET_DATA_DIR and interval as above.
#
# Energy uses the same sampling cadence as telemetry. RAPL needs readable
# /sys/class/powercap/*/energy_uj for the service user; NVIDIA uses nvidia-smi in PATH.
#
# systemd --user and system services often start with a minimal PATH. The install scripts set a
# standard PATH in the unit (includes /snap/bin for Docker snap). Override only if needed (e.g. CUDA first):
# PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:/snap/bin:/var/lib/snapd/snap/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
#
# If ``docker`` is still not found, set an absolute binary (Fleet resolves this for ``docker_argv`` jobs):
# FLEET_DOCKER_BIN=/path/to/docker
# A bare name works too (Fleet expands via PATH), e.g. FLEET_DOCKER_BIN=docker — do not rely on a non-existent path.
# When the Docker CLI is missing but Podman is installed, Fleet uses ``podman`` automatically; set
# FLEET_NO_PODMAN_FALLBACK=1 to disable that and fail fast instead.
